What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I think the course will be better organized and flow better in years to come, and given the relevance of the subject matter, I would recommend the class.

It's a course for studying themes of identity and citizenship in two countries that have had volatile and fast-changing government structures and political rule. Very interesting from a sociological and anthropological standpoint.
Excellent course, wonderful readings, and outstanding professors!
